ersatile design with high flexibility to process crudes of various api gravity and with high degree of automation mrpl has a design capacity to process  million metric tonnes per annum and is the only refinery in india to have two hydrocrackers producing premium diesel high cetaneit also has a polypropylene unit with a capacity of  mtannum it is also the only refinery in india to have two ccrs producing unleaded petrol of high octane currently the refinery is processing about  million tonnes of crude per year and had a turnover of us  billion during last year mrpl which was a joint sector company become a psu subsequent on acquisition of its majority shares by ongc as on  april   shares are held by ongc  shares are held by hpcl and remaining shares are with public and financial institutions mrpl has also been declared as miniratna a mini jewel by government of india in  before acquisition by ongc in march  mrpl was a joint venture oil refinery promoted by ms hindustan petroleum corporation limited hpcl a public sector company and ms iril  associates av birla group mrpl was set up in  with the initial processing capacity of  million metric tonnes per annum that was later expanded to the present capacity of  million metric tonnes per annum the refinery was conceived to maximise middle distillates with capability to process light to heavy and sour to sweet crudes with  to  api gravity on  march  ongc acquired the total shareholding of av birla group and further infused equity capital of rs billion thus making mrpl a majorityheld subsidiary of ongc the lenders also agreed to the debt restructuring package drp proposed by ongc which included inter alia conversion up to rs  core of their loans into equity subsequently ongc has acquired equity allotted to the lenders pursuant to drp raising ongcs holding in mrpl to  percent see alsoedit list of oil refineries in india referencesedit  httpwwwmoneycontrolcomfinancialsmrplprofitlossmrp httpnewskarnatakacommangaloreyouthstoben